olive oil
1 cucumber
1 apple
1 Brown Onion
1 carrot
½ lime
1 drizzle rice wine vinegar
1 bag herbs
1 packet pulled chicken
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 drizzle sesame oil
1 packet sriracha
1 tsp soy sauce
1 bag Mixed Leaves
1 packet roasted peanuts
1 packet mayonnaise

• Thinly slice cucumber into half-moons. Slice apple into thin wedges. Thinly
slice onion. Grate the carrot. Cut lime into wedges.
• In small heatproof bowl, combine onion, a drizzle of rice wine vinegar, a
splash of water and a good pinch of sugar and salt.
• Microwave onion in 30 seconds bursts, until just softened. Set aside.

• Tear the herbs.
• In a medium bowl, combine pulled chicken, sweet chilli sauce,
mayonnaise, herbs and a drizzle of sesame oil.

• In a large bowl, combine sriracha, the soy sauce, a generous squeeze of
lime juice and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.
• Just before serving, add mixed leaves, carrot, cucumber and apple. Toss
to coat.

• Drain pickled onion.
• Divide salad between bowls and top with Southeast Asian-style chicken.
• Top with roasted peanuts and pickled onion to serve. Enjoy!